<heading>list - List active sessions.</heading>

<rule/>

<heading level="2">
Usage
</heading>

<pre>
  list
</pre>

<heading level="2">
Description
</heading>

<paragraph>
Lists all active runtime sessions and their connection
details.
</paragraph>

<paragraph>
Sessions are listed by key with attached clients, homes,
and active flows. The current session is marked with
an asterisk.
</paragraph>

<heading level="2">
Examples
</heading>

<pre>
list
  List all active sessions.
</pre>

<paragraph>
Use session list to see which sessions are active and
which one you are currently using.
</paragraph>

<heading level="2">
See also
</heading>

<paragraph>
attach, current, detach, man
</paragraph>
